To find the median of two sorted arrays of different sizes with O(1) space complexity and O(n) time complexity, you can use the following function:

```
function median(arr1, arr2) {
  // Sort the arrays
  arr1.sort();
  arr2.sort();

  // Find the middle index of arr1
  const middleIndex1 = Math.floor(arr1.length / 2);

  // Find the middle index of arr2
  const middleIndex2 = Math.floor(arr2.length / 2);

  // Find the median by taking the element at the middle index of arr1 and arr2
  const median = arr1[middleIndex1] + arr2[middleIndex2];

  // Return the median
  return median;
}
```

This function sorts both arrays in O(n) time complexity and then finds the median by taking the element at the middle index of each array. The median is then returned.

